en than they will win.\", \"from\": 3681, \"to\": 3730, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Stick with the most probable outcome and you are more likely to be correct.\", \"from\": 3731, \"to\": 3806, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the most probable outcome\", \"from\": 3742, \"to\": 3767}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Throwing in anecdotes about a team, an athlete or an event demonstrates a knowledge that goes beyond what's unfolding live.\", \"from\": 3808, \"to\": 3931, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anecdotes\", \"from\": 3820, \"to\": 3829}, {\"ngram\": \"a team\", \"from\": 3836, \"to\": 3842}, {\"ngram\": \"an athlete\", \"from\": 3844, \"to\": 3854}, {\"ngram\": \"an event\", \"from\": 3858, \"to\": 3866}, {\"ngram\": \"a knowledge\", \"from\": 3880, \"to\": 3891}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These can range from statistics of wins or losses, historical information about the origins of a sport or quirky information about prominent people in each sport.\", \"from\": 3932, \"to\": 4094, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"statistics\", \"from\": 3953, \"to\": 3963}, {\"ngram\": \"wins\", \"from\": 3967, \"to\": 3971}, {\"ngram\": \"losses\", \"from\": 3975, \"to\": 3981}, {\"ngram\": \"historical information\", \"from\": 3983, \"to\": 4005}, {\"ngram\": \"the origins\", \"from\": 4012, \"to\": 4023}, {\"ngram\": \"a sport or quirky information\", \"from\": 4027, \"to\": 4056}, {\"ngram\": \"prominent people\", \"from\": 4063, \"to\": 4079}, {\"ngram\": \"each sport\", \"from\": 4083, \"to\": 4093}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only for interesting, trivial, fun facts, how else would we know thatIreland wanted to host the 1940 Olympic Gamesor thatPaul Mescal played underage intercounty football for Kildare?\", \"from\": 4095, \"to\": 4277, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4221, \"end\": 4227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mescal,_Arizona\", \"score\": 0.8977174706268789, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mescal\", \